cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes follower demographics on Twitter, which is a social network platform.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper may involve software tools and techniques for data collection and analysis.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the social and demographic aspects of the 2016 U.S. presidential campaign.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is a possible category as the paper analyzes social influence and polarization among the followers of the two candidates.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper uses profile images of followers as one of the data sources for demographic analysis.
